Maureen Ihua-Maduenyi A Caverton Helicopter was forced to land on Sunday after losing an engine. It was gathered that there were no casualties in the incident that occurred in Escravos, Delta State. The Bell 412 Helicopter was said to be flying from a Floating Storage and Offloading terminal to MEREN field when it lost an engine and was diverted to land in Escravos. The Accident Investigation Bureau confirmed the incident but had yet to make a formal statement on it as of the time of filing this report. Copyright PUNCH.
